_2527786\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gbo1665702921950.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gbo1665702921950.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gbo1665702921950.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gbo1665702921950\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Minimizing Access Paths\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The system load caused by the access paths is expressed as access stress rates. You can shorten access paths and minimize access stress rates by storing redundant data to increase ease of access (denormalization) or changing the user view.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__p_d45869e1_d45870e1_d45871e1\">Denormalization has a major impact on the application model and therefore on the application. Denormalization is usually considered before changing the user-view, because the latter affects the information processing capabilities offered to the end-users.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__p_d45872e1_d45873e1_d45874e1\">Denormalization measures include the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__li_d22946e1_d22947e1_d22948e1\">Adding redundant relationships between entities of the Uniface application model\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__li_d22949e1_d22950e1_d22951e1\">Combining separate entities into a single entity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__li_d22952e1_d22953e1_d22954e1\">Splitting an entity horizontally by dividing different sets of rows in separate entities\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__li_d22955e1_d22956e1_d22957e1\">Splitting an entity vertically by dividing different sets of columns in separate entities\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__li_d22958e1_d22959e1_d22960e1\">Replicating entities\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__li_d22961e1_d22962e1_d22963e1\">Temporarily isolating rows in a separate entity—isolating a set of related rows of different entities into a single entity for intensive processing\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__li_d22964e1_d22965e1_d22966e1\">Adding redundant attributes, for example, for storing processing results or storing state information\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__p_d45875e1_d45876e1_d45877e1\">Although it is an effective way to improve performance, denormalization should be applied carefully because it makes the application harder to maintain. Also, a denormalized application model no longer reflects the business correctly.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gbo1665702921950__p_d45878e1_d45879e1_d45880e1\">The listed denormalization measures are modifications to the data model. Several products implement denormalization on a more technical level, leaving the data model as it is. For example, some databases support table replication, and data warehousing products temporarily isolate data.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527786\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527786\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Minimizing Access Paths Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Minimizing Access Paths The system load caused by the access paths is expressed as access stress rates. You can shorten access paths and minimize access stress rates by storing redundant data to increase ease of access (denormalization) or changing the user view. Denormalization has a major impact on the application model and therefore on the application. Denormalization is usually considered before changing the user-view, because the latter affects the information processing capabilities offered to the end-users. Denormalization measures include the following: Adding redundant relationships between entities of the Uniface application model Combining separate entities into a single entity Splitting an entity horizontally by dividing different sets of rows in separate entities Splitting an entity vertically by dividing different sets of columns in separate entities Replicating entities Temporarily isolating rows in a separate entity—isolating a set of related rows of different entities into a single entity for intensive processing Adding redundant attributes, for example, for storing processing results or storing state information Although it is an effective way to improve performance, denormalization should be applied carefully because it makes the application harder to maintain. Also, a denormalized application model no longer reflects the business correctly. The listed denormalization measures are modifications to the data model. Several products implement denormalization on a more technical level, leaving the data model as it is. For example, some databases support table replication, and data warehousing products temporarily isolate data. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}